<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idab6b1b46-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s9284"><num value="9284">§ 9284.</num><heading> Medal of honor: duplicate medal</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A person awarded a medal of honor shall, upon written application of that person, be issued, without charge, one duplicate medal of honor with ribbons and appurtenances. Such duplicate medal of honor shall be marked, in such manner as the Secretary of the Air Force may determine, as a duplicate or for display purposes only.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idab6b1b47-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/107/107/dA/tV/s553/c/1/A">Pub. L. 107–107, div. A, title V, § 553(c)(1)(A)</ref>, <date date="2001-12-28">Dec. 28, 2001</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/115/1116">115 Stat. 1116</ref>, § 8754; renumbered § 9284, <ref href="/us/pl/115/232/dA/tVIII/s806/b/11">Pub. L. 115–232, div. A, title VIII, § 806(b)(11)</ref>, <date date="2018-08-13">Aug. 13, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/1833">132 Stat. 1833</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
